text: Dinas may refer to: == Places == ===England=== * Dinas, an area of Padstow, Cornwall * Castle an Dinas, St Columb Major, an Iron Age hillfort at the summit of Castle Downs, Cornwall * Treryn Dinas, a headland near Treen, on the Penwith peninsula, Cornwall * Trereen Dinas, an Iron Age promontory fort at Gurnard's Head, Cornwall === Wales === * Dinas, Gwynedd, a large hamlet near Bontnewydd, Caernarfon ** Dinas railway station, on the narrow gauge Welsh Highland Railway ** Dinas (FR) railway station, disused Festiniog Railway station * Dinas Cross, a village and community in Pembrokeshire ** Dinas Island, a peninsula in the community of Dinas Cross *Dinas Dinlle, a small settlement in Gwynedd *Dinas Emrys, a hillock near Beddgelert, Gwynedd *Dinas Mawddwy, a town and community in Gwynedd * Dinas Powys, a village and community in the Vale of Glamorgan ** Dinas Powys railway station **Dinas Powys hillfort * Dinas Rhondda, a village near Tonypandy, Rhondda Cynon Taf ** Dinas Rhondda railway station *Castell Dinas, a hillfort and castle in southern Powys *Pen Dinas, a large hill in Penparcau, on the coast of Ceredigion === Philippines === * Dinas, Zamboanga del Sur, a municipality ==People== * Arley Dinas (born 1974), a former Colombian football player * Thanasis Dinas (born 1989), Greek footballer ==Other uses== * Dinas (weevil), a beetle genus in the tribe Sciaphilini ==See also== *
